rlm-lhdir [hook-name]

Run lefthook on every tracked-or-untracked-but-not-ignored file
under the current directory, recursively, regardless of git
stage state.

Defaults to the `pre-commit` hook; pass another stage name as
the first argument, e.g. `rlm-lhdir pre-push`.

Equivalent to:

    git ls-files --cached --others --exclude-standard . \
        | lefthook run <hook> --files-from-stdin

Useful for linting / formatting an entire subdirectory without
having to stage everything first.

Aliases: lhdir, lhd (and rlm-lhd)
